The powers are also somewhat similar, but because Germany has a federal structure, it also has these courts of account at the level of individual Länder - in this the system differs slightly from ours.
The BRH can only control federal money, which in our country is state funds.
Public funds, which are managed by the counties and municipalities, are controlled at the level of the Federal Court of Auditors.
As far as the legislation there is concerned, is it simpler than ours?
