Do I have to turn into a lab tech and suppress my natural inclinations?
The three years before me have developed into a purgatory of ignorance and isolation.
The only openly conservative professor was Norman Stone, a professor of modern history who was based at my faculty.
He was hated not only for being a conservative, but also for being Margaret Thatcher's foreign policy adviser and one of her speechwriters.
He was barely there.
He hated the place for its guilt and pettiness and for its propensity for a Marxist-determinist view of history.
In 1997, he became a professor at Bilkent University in Ankara, Turkey.
"You won't be happy here", he told me.
I began driving from Oxford to my parents' house in London, seeking refuge with my unbiased metropolitan friends and family.
